There are so many things
wrong with that picture

02:15.299 --> 02:17.533
that I don't even think I'm offended.

02:17.601 --> 02:19.401
Yeah, what's wrong with it?

02:19.469 --> 02:21.369
I think it's pretty good.

02:21.437 --> 02:23.805
Well, first of all, I'm not a cheerleader.

02:23.873 --> 02:26.207
And second of all, I don't have buckteeth.

02:26.275 --> 02:28.175
And third of all,
I don't walk around saying,

02:28.243 --> 02:30.844
"I'm Ariel, I'm Ariel!"

02:30.912 --> 02:33.680
But other than that,
I think you, uh, you nailed it.

02:33.747 --> 02:35.014
It's a caricature.

02:35.082 --> 02:37.049
It's not supposed to look exactly like you.

02:37.117 --> 02:40.752
It's supposed to tell the truth
about what you're like inside.

02:40.820 --> 02:43.021
And you're right, I think I nailed it.

02:43.090 --> 02:45.392
Good morning, all.

02:47.028 --> 02:49.362
Wow, Bridge, you did all those?

02:49.430 --> 02:51.031
Looks like you've been really busy.

02:51.098 --> 02:52.065
Yep.

02:52.132 --> 02:54.834
Why the sudden interest in art?

02:54.901 --> 02:56.769
Please, Bridgette' not interested in art.

02:56.836 --> 02:59.371
Bridgette is interested in
Finn who is interested in art.

02:59.439 --> 03:00.472
Hey!

03:00.540 --> 03:01.773
Oh, yeah? Who's this Finn?

03:01.841 --> 03:03.374
Bridgette's boyfriend.

03:03.442 --> 03:05.543
He is not. He's not.

03:05.610 --> 03:08.178
He's just a friend that happens to be a boy.

03:08.246 --> 03:09.980
And, uh, it's not the same thing.

03:10.048 --> 03:11.014
Okay.

03:11.082 --> 03:12.549
All right, if you say so.

03:12.616 --> 03:15.217
Does Mom know about this?

03:15.285 --> 03:17.786
Well, I was going to mention
it to her this morning,

03:17.854 --> 03:19.487
but she got up and went to work

03:19.555 --> 03:20.755
before I got up,

03:20.823 --> 03:22.156
so I didn't get to.

03:22.223 --> 03:23.624
Thank you.

03:23.692 --> 03:25.659
Well, I'm here, and I'm all ears.

03:25.727 --> 03:27.961
So tell me a little bit
more about this friend

03:28.029 --> 03:29.730
who happens to be a boy.

03:29.797 --> 03:31.364
He's really nice.

03:31.432 --> 03:33.433
And he sits in front of me in math class.

03:33.500 --> 03:37.736
He's into a lot of the same
really cool stuff that I am.

03:37.803 --> 03:40.138
He's really nice to me, too.

03:40.206 --> 03:43.374
He plays with me and
Bridgette on the playground.

03:43.442 --> 03:45.341
Hmm, okay, I got it.

03:45.409 --> 03:47.375
Finn is cool. Finn is nice.

03:47.443 --> 03:49.677
Come on, dishes into the sink.

03:49.745 --> 03:51.279
We're leaving in five minutes.

03:54.316 --> 03:55.016
See you later.

03:55.084 --> 03:56.584
Okay, see you later.

03:56.652 --> 03:57.652
Later, Pop.

03:57.720 --> 03:59.654
Later.

03:59.722 --> 04:01.522
Morning, Keelin. Morning, Keelin.

04:01.590 --> 04:04.492
Did you sleep well? Did you sleep well?

04:04.559 --> 04:07.329
Do you think maybe this morning
Do you think maybe this morning

04:07.397 --> 04:09.432
you could try to answer
you could try to answer

04:09.500 --> 04:10.867
my questions my questions

04:10.935 --> 04:13.068
instead of repeating them?
instead of repeating them?

04:13.136 --> 04:15.971
Any idea how this girl was able
to break out of this facility?

04:16.039 --> 04:19.175
I mean, I know the name is
Mariposa Psychiatric Hospital,

04:19.243 --> 04:21.209
but it is part of the prison system.

04:21.278 --> 04:22.512
Based on that tape,

04:22.579 --> 04:24.981
that girls doesn't seem terribly aggressive.

04:25.048 --> 04:27.049
To be honest, I'm a little flummoxed.

04:27.117 --> 04:28.484
I think we both are.

04:28.552 --> 04:31.787
Well, obviously, we have a security presence

04:31.855 --> 04:33.089
here at Mariposa Psych,

04:33.156 --> 04:35.024
but in the wing where Keelin resides

04:35.092 --> 04:37.026
it's fairly benign.

04:37.093 --> 04:39.328
Those patients are all
approaching the age of majority.

04:39.396 --> 04:41.330
They're within a year of being released.

04:41.397 --> 04:42.798
So as part of their treatment,

04:42.866 --> 04:44.633
they're afforded much more freedom

04:44.701 --> 04:46.001
than the other wings enjoy.

04:46.069 --> 04:50.038
And the vast majority of
our patients are minors,

04:50.106 --> 04:53.675
so we see very few attempted escapes.

04:53.743 --> 04:56.611
I know that's not much help.

04:56.679 --> 04:58.280
So, uh, who are we looking for?

04:58.348 --> 04:59.983
What can you tell us about her,

05:00.050 --> 05:03.186
other than the fact that she
repeats whatever anybody tells her?

05:03.253 --> 05:06.389
Well, her full name is Keelin McKinney.

05:06.457 --> 05:11.560
And three years ago,
right before her 15th birthday,

05:11.628 --> 05:13.796
she had an affair with her history teacher.

05:13.863 --> 05:16.799
And about five months into it,

05:16.866 --> 05:18.934
the history teacher broke it off.

05:19.002 --> 05:20.635
A week later, she follows him home,

05:20.703 --> 05:22.003
ties him up in his bed

05:22.071 --> 05:24.072
and shoots him 12 times
with her father's pistol.

05:24.139 --> 05:26.874
The police arrive.

05:26.942 --> 05:29.811
She's just sitting there, unresponsive,

05:29.878 --> 05:33.047
and she slipped into a catatonic state.

05:33.115 --> 05:36.183
And, finally, two months ago,
she came out of it.

05:36.251 --> 05:37.518
So that parroting that you saw

05:37.586 --> 05:39.553
on the video-- that's called echolalia.

05:39.621 --> 05:41.355
We almost always encounter it

05:41.423 --> 05:42.857
when catatonic patients awaken.

05:42.924 --> 05:46.127
But having said that,
I've never seen the phenomena

05:46.194 --> 05:48.295
present itself in quite the
way it has with Keelin.

05:48.363 --> 05:51.565
The depth of her recall is extraordinary.

05:51.633 --> 05:54.735
Sometimes she spends whole therapy sessions

05:54.803 --> 05:56.804
parroting the previous session.

05:56.872 --> 05:58.639
Or... she did.

05:58.707 --> 06:00.107
I don't understand.

06:00.175 --> 06:02.910
All she could do was repeat
back what people said to her,

06:02.978 --> 06:05.179
and yet she's within a year of her release?

06:05.247 --> 06:06.780
She was sentenced as a minor.

06:06.848 --> 06:08.582
She's about to turn 18.

06:08.650 --> 06:11.986
And strange as it seems,
the echolalia-- that's progress.

06:12.054 --> 06:13.921
After three years of total silence,

06:13.989 --> 06:16.023
it's Keelin's way of
coming back into the world.

06:16.091 --> 06:19.426
And you have no idea how
she was able to get out?

06:19.494 --> 06:22.830
Maybe she snuck in the
back of a delivery truck.

06:22.898 --> 06:24.064
Hitched a ride out.

06:24.132 --> 06:28.302
Maybe someone left a wrong door open.

06:28.369 --> 06:30.704
None of the orderlies or the guards

06:30.772 --> 06:31.938
are willing to admit

06:32.006 --> 06:34.007
they know anything about what happened.

06:34.075 --> 06:35.675
I think they're afraid for their jobs.

06:35.743 --> 06:37.711
But I'm hoping they'll be more cooperative

06:37.779 --> 06:38.979
when policemen are asking the questions.

06:39.047 --> 06:40.513
I'd be happy to talk to them

06:40.581 --> 06:41.948
and take a look around.

06:42.016 --> 06:44.817
Dr. Woodel, this girl Keelin,
what's your feeling?

06:44.885 --> 06:46.619
Do you think she's dangerous?

06:46.687 --> 06:48.521
I'd like to say no.

06:48.589 --> 06:50.156
That I'm confident that my work with her

06:50.224 --> 06:51.724
has cured her of those impulses,

06:51.792 --> 06:53.626
but I obviously misjudged Keelin.

06:53.694 --> 06:55.161
We all did.

06:55.229 --> 06:59.398
So I can't answer that for sure.

06:59.466 --> 07:01.500
So where do we start?

07:01.568 --> 07:04.169
I thought maybe you could
check out the girl's room

07:04.237 --> 07:05.604
while I walk the grounds.

07:05.672 --> 07:07.706
It's right upstairs, room 306.

07:07.774 --> 07:10.208
Maybe something will come to you, you know?

